
[1]cue

   CUE, n. [L.]

   1. The tail; the end of a thing; as the long curl of a wig, or a long
   roll of hair.

   2. The last words of a speech, which a player, who is to answer,
   catches and regards as an intimation to begin. A hint given to an actor
   on the stage, what or when to speak.

   3. A hint; an intimation; a short direction.

   4. The part which any man is to play in his turn.

   Were it my cue to fight.

   5. Humor; turn or temper of mind. [Vulgar.]

   6. A farthing, or farthings worth.

   7. The straight rod, used in playing billiards.
